  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 24 g
  fiber: 1 g
  sodium: 1260 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pulled-pork-crunchy-cuke-bowls-648886ff8b1fa4d79c445136
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
---

Gently massage @Microwavable Rice{1%unit} in package to break up grains. Partially
open package and microwave according to package instructions, ~{90%seconds}.
Fluff with a #fork{}.

> To make fluffing easier, transfer to a small #bowl{} first.

Wash and dry produce.

Thinly slice @Mini Cucumber{1%unit} into rounds. Thinly slice @Scallions{2%unit},
separating whites from greens.

In a small bowl, combine cucumber, @Rice Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, a pinch of
@Sugar{1/4%tsp}, @Salt{pinch}, and @Pepper{pinch}. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and
microwave until sugar dissolves, ~{15-30%seconds}. Stir and set aside to pickle.

In a second small bowl, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @Sriracha{1%unit}, and
2 tsp water.

Place @Pulled Pork{8%ounce} in a medium bowl; shred into bite-size pieces using
your hands or 2 #forks{}.

> Using your hands is much faster.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Add scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Add pulled pork and @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}; cook, stirring occasionally,
until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> No stove available? In a large bowl, combine pulled pork, Fry Seasoning, and
> scallion whites. Cover tightly with plastic wrap and microwave until warmed
> through, 2-3 minutes.

Divide rice between bowls. Top with pulled pork, pickled cucumber
(draining first), and scallion greens. Drizzle with as much Sriracha mayo as you
like and serve.

> Pulled Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.